Catherine Swietlicki, Spanish Christian Cabala. The Works of Luis de Leon, Santa Teresa de Jesus, and San Juan de la Cruz (Univ. Missouri 1986), i.e., St. Teresa and the Cabala generally at 51-81, re Sufis and the seven castles at 62-66; Swietlicki cited by L&lt;U+00F3&gt;pez-Baralt, Islam in Spanish Literature at 127-131, 134.↩
&quot;Convivencia&quot; signifies &quot;living together&quot; in Spanish, and may refer to a early medieval Golden Age ideal, in which the three faiths would share their cultures in peace. Prof. As&lt;U+00ED&gt;n contributed to the reification of the third pillar.↩


